25|$|The series spans 50 {{years of}} Quatermain's life, from 18 to 68; {{at the start}} of the {{foundation}} novel King Solomon's Mines, he has just turned 55. Physically, he is small, wiry, and unattractive, <b>with</b> <b>a</b> <b>beard</b> and short hair that sticks up. His one skill is his marksmanship, where he has no equal. Quatermain is aware that as a professional hunter, he has helped to destroy his beloved wild free places of Africa. In old age he hunts without pleasure, having no other means of making a living.|$|E
